HEADWORD: Testiness
<hw>Tes"ti*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
state of being testy; fretfulness; petulance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Testiness</qex> is a disposition or aptness to be angry.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

